Reasoning: The paper deals with the fundamental tradeoff between rate and bandwidth in communication channels, specifically in the context of error exponents. This falls under the domain of information theory and communication systems, which are covered by the cs.IT and cs.COMM sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of different signaling schemes, which is related to signal processing and modulation techniques, covered by the cs.SI sub-category. The consideration of fading channels and full CSI also suggests a possible connection to wireless networks and networked systems, covered by the cs.NI sub-category. Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also be relevant to machine learning and optimization, covered by the cs.MS sub-category.
